<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="343" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,222,427]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
This is an undescribed endemic Madagascan species discovered by ABRI collectors at Mont d'Ambre, which has been referred to in unpublished reports as 
<emphasis box="[649,785,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1916" box="[649,781,258,283]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hollandi">A. hollandi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
T.B. Larsen (pers. comm.) will describe it as new. The yellow hyaline markings at the apex of the hind wing suggest affinities with no other known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1896" box="[1242,1345,295,318]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1242,1345,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Artitropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<figureCitation box="[158,272,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="42.[151,250,936,958]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,490,904]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1436,482,911]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 39. Pinned adult male of Artitropa sp. SCC 03, collected on Dracaena sp., Mont d’Ambre, northern Madagascar, Jan 2003 [TCEC]. 1.5 x life size, scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253571/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
Figure 
<number box="[241,272,331,355]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
); however, these markings are not present on the only other specimen reared. T.B. Larsen (pers. comm. 
<number box="[151,209,367,391]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) has examined these markings under a microscope and notes they are well defined, fully scaled and symmetrical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253571/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" targetBox="[163,1427,490,904]" targetPageId="42">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,936,988]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,936,958]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">FIGURE 39.</emphasis>
Pinned adult male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1896" box="[511,604,937,958]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,604,937,958]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Artitropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. SCC03, collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[861,962,937,958]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis box="[861,962,937,958]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Dracaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., Mont d’Ambre, northern Madagascar, Jan 2003 [TCEC]. 1.5 x life size, scale bar = 1 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253572/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" targetBox="[151,1436,1041,1597]" targetPageId="42">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1621,1674]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1621,1643]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">FIGURE 40.</emphasis>
Caterpillars of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1896" box="[443,536,1622,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[443,536,1622,1643]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Artitropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. SCC03, collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[790,891,1623,1644]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis box="[790,891,1623,1644]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Dracaena</emphasis>
